#X text 269 104 Here we have a sequencer in the style of a "Drum Machine".
We have a series of toggles whose values are stored in an array. Actually
we have two tracks \, each in a horizontal line and stored in a different
array.;
#X text 269 169 The [count] object is used to generate the indexes
of our sequence \, then we use [tabread] objects to output values from
the arrays. The stored values are only 0 or 1 \, and if it is "1" \,
[sel 1] outputs a bang that we use to trigger a sample.;
